  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Men or non-pregnant women

          -  A diagnosis of symptomatic paroxysmal or recently persistent atrial fibrillation with
             a documented successful cardioversion within 4 months of the procedure

          -  Documented treatment failure or intolerance of at least 1 anti-arrhythmic medication
             used to control atrial fibrillation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindication to MRI, such as implanted incompatible metal prosthesis, or subject
             size exceeds bore or table limits

          -  Allergy to gadolinium-based contrast agent

          -  Previous atrial fibrillation ablation

          -  Renal dysfunction (estimated GFR &lt;60 mL/min/1.73m2) within 6 months

          -  Unwilling to provide informed consent for this protocol
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
